<p align=center><font FACE="Arial"><font color="#0080FF"><font size=5><b>SOUTH AFRICAN<br>
COAL RESEARCH &amp; DEVELOPMENT: 1995-1996<br>
</font></b></font></font> </p>
<p align=center><font size=2><b>REPORT PREPARED BY THE CHAMBER OF MINES OF SOUTH AFRICA ON BEHALF<br clear=all>
OF THE SOUTH AFRICAN MEMBERS OF THE ICCR FOR THE MEETING OF THE </b></font></p>
<p align=center><font color="#800000"><font size=4><b>INTERNATIONAL COMMITTEE FOR COAL RESEARCH</b></font></font></p>
<p align=center><font size=2><b><u>TOKYO, JAPAN</u></b></font></p>
<p align=center><font size=2><b>OCTOBER 1996</b></font> </p>
<hr noshade width=80%>
<p align=left>The International Committee for Coal Research (ICCR) was formed in 1974, and has the following country members: 
Australia, Belgium, Canada, France, Germany, Japan, New Zealand, Poland, South Africa, Spain, United States of America, 
and United Kingdom. </p>
<p align=left>The ICCR serves as a forum for the major coal producing and utilising countries to collaborate on research and development, 
and to discuss matters of common interest. Committee meetings are held annually, and a conference is held every three years. </p>
<p align=left>The South African members are <a href="http://www.bullion.org.za/cvs/stewart.htm">Dr J M Stewart, Mining Consultant</a>, <a href="http://www.bullion.org.za">Chamber of Mines of South Africa</a> (country convenor), 
Mr R&#160;P Mohring (Director, Ingwe Coal Corporation), <a href="mailto:KAPLAN@egoli.min.wits.ac.za">Prof. H&#160;R Phillips</a> (Head, <a href="http://www-eng.wits.ac.za/min/min_home.html">Department of Mining Engineering, University 
of the Witwatersrand</a>), <a href="mailto:TONYS@mepta.pwv.gov.za">Dr A&#160;D Surridge</a> (Director: Electrical Energy, <a href="http://www.polity.org.za/lists/govdepts.html#DOMEA">Department of Minerals and Energy</a>), and <a href="mailto:a39173@tri.eskom.co.za">Dr M van der 
Riet</a> (<a href="http://www.eskom.co.za">Chief Consultant: Fuels Combustion, Eskom</a>). The next annual meeting of the International Committee for Coal Research 
(ICCR) will be held on 21 - 24 October 1996 in Tokyo, Japan. A feature of the meeting is the presentation by each member 
country of a report on the coal R&amp;D carried out in that country during the previous year. </p>
<p align=left>A copy of the South African report is attached. Requests for collaboration should in the first instance be addressed to the 
convenor for the ICCR in South Africa at the following address:<font FACE="Arial"></p>
<p align=center><font size=1><strong>Dr J M Stewart<br>
Mining Consultant<br>
</strong></font><a href="http://www.bullion.org.za"><font size=1><strong>Chamber of Mines of South Africa</strong></font></a><font size=1><strong><br>
