<p><b>1. Safety and Health </b></p>
<p>1.1 <u>Explosions, fires and dust</u> </p>
<ul>
<li>Methane prediction in collieries </li>
<li>Fire and ignition hazards in coal mines </li>
<li>The identification of methods to reduce the risk of explosions and fires caused by frictional ignition hazards </li>
<li>Reduce explosion risks and improve safety and health conditions by better ventilation practices in mechanical miner 
headings </li>
<li>Reduce the risk associated with methane gas produced or accumulated and emitting from goafs and abandoned areas </li>
<li>Data capture effectiveness of scrubber systems on mechanical miners operating in larger roadways </li>
<li>Develop an intrinsically safe protection device for a cap lamp battery </li>
<li>Systems to limit coal dust and methane explosions in coal mines </li>
</ul>
<p>1.2 <u>Transport and machinery</u> </p>
<ul>
<li>Remove operator from continuous miner </li>
<li>Guidelines for the development of training manuals focused on the safer use of conveyors, shuttle cars and tractor 
trailers (mobile machines) </li>
</ul>
<p>1.3 <u>Support</u> </p>
<ul>
<li>Identification of causes of unsafe acts or neglect resulting in roof falls or sidewall accidents in coal mines </li>
<li>Coal pillar design procedures </li>
<li>The effect of discontinuities on coal pillar strength </li>
<li>Review of current design methodologies to improve the safety or roof support systems, particularly in the face area, in 
collieries </li>
</ul>
<p>1.4 <u>Communication </u></p>
