<p align=center><font face="Arial">&#160;&#160;</font><font face="Arial"><font color="#0080FF"><font size=6><strong>SOUTH AFRICA, RAINBOW 
NATION OF MINERAL WEALTH</font></strong></font></font></p>
<p align=center><font color="#FF0000"><font size=3><em>A paper presented by:</em></font></font><font size=4><br>
</font><font size=3>Mr A. J. (At) du Plessis</font><font size=2>, </font><font size=3><br>
Outgoing president, Chamber of Mines of South Africa,</font><font size=2> </font><br>
<font size=1>on <br>
</font>Wednesday, 4 December 1996<br>
<font size=1>at the </font><font size=2><strong><br>
</strong></font><font size=4><strong>102nd Annual Northwest Mining Association Convention</strong> </font><br>
<font size=2>held in Spokane, Washington, USA.</font></p>
<hr>
<p align=center><font color="#FF0000"><font size=4><strong>CONTENTS</strong></font></font></p>
<blockquote>
<blockquote>
<blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p align=left><a href="#INTRODUCTION">Introduction<br>
</a><a href="#ENVIRONMENTAL">Environmental Changes<br>
</a><a href="#PRODUCTION">Production<br>
</a><a href="#GOVERNMENT'S">Government's Role<br>
</a><a href="#EMPOWERMENT">Empowerment<br>
