</p>
<p align=center><a name="ANNEXUREB1"><font size=4><b>ANNEXURE B1<br></b></font></a></p>
<p align=left><b><u>AGREEMENT BETWEEN BLYVOORUITZICHT GOLD MINING COMPANY LIMITED AND THE 
NATIONAL UNION OF MINEWORKERS<br>
</u></b>It is agreed that all employees presently employed at category 1 level at Doornfontein Section will be promoted to category 2 
level on conditions of employment as apply at Blyvooruitzicht Section. It is further agreed that all employees presently 
employed at category 2 level at Doornfontein will be promoted to category 3 level on conditions of employment as apply at 
Blyvooruitzicht. This upliftment exercise will be completed within six months from the date of signature of the 1996 Wage 
Review Agreement, as employees will undergo training before being upgraded.<br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p align=center><a name="ANNEXUREB2"><font size=4><b>ANNEXURE B2</b></font></a></p>
<p align=left><b><u>AGREEMENT BETWEEN EAST RAND PROPRIETARY MINES LIMITED AND THE NATIONAL UNION 
OF MINEWORKERS<br>
</u></b>1. It is agreed that category 3 production employees (i.e. Stoping and Development (face)) will be upgraded to category 4 
following successful completion of prescribed training modules to equip them to carry out any team task as the situation 
demands it. It is envisaged that such training will be completed by the end of March 1997 at the latest.<br>
</p>
<p align=left>2. The employees affected by 1 above will be remunerated at the category 4 minimum rate.<br>
</p>
<p align=center>3. The NUM accepts that there will be no increase in fixed costs to the mine as a result of bonus scheme renegotiations.<br>
<br></p>
<p align=center><br>
<a name="ANNEXUREB3"><font size=4><b>ANNEXURE B3<br>
</b></font></a><b></b></p>
<p><b><u>AGREEMENT BETWEEN HARMONY GOLD MINING COMPANY LIMITED AND THE NATIONAL 
UNION OF MINEWORKERS<br>
</u></b>It is agreed that discussions will take place at mine level regarding the mine calendar.<br>
<br>
</p>
<p align=center><a name="ANNEXUREB4"><font size=4><b>ANNEXURE B4</b></font></a></p>
<p align=left><a name="ANNEXUREB4"><b><br>
</b></a><b><u>AGREEMENT BETWEEN DURBAN ROODEPOORT DEEP LIMITED<br>
<br>
</u></b></p>
<p><b></b>&nbsp;</p>
<p align=center><a name="ANNEXUREB5"><font size=4><b>ANNEXURE B5</b></font></a><b><br>
</b></p>
<p><b><u>AGREEMENT BETWEEN INGWE COAL CORPORATION LIMITED AND THE NATIONAL UNION OF 
MINEWORKERS IN RESPECT OF DOUGLAS COLLIERY<br>
</u></b>It is agreed that the wage rates of staff employees at Douglas Colliery will be aligned with the staff wage rates applicable at 
other Ingwe mines which are party to the Chamber of Mines labour agreements. The alignment will be implemented as 
follows:<br>
</p>
<p>1. Staff employees at Douglas, surface and underground, will receive an increase equal to the difference between the 
employee's current wage and the revised 1996 minimum wage rate for staff employees at Douglas.<br>
</p>
<p>2. The alignment will include the re-classification of certain staff occupations at Douglas as non-staff occupations in cases 
where such staff occupations are not classified as staff occupations at other Ingwe mines which are party to the Chamber of 
Mines labour agreements.<br>
</p>
<p>The following will be applicable regarding the classification: <br>
</p>
<p>2.1 <u>Guarantees<br>
</u></p>
<p>The following guarantees will apply to employees who will be re-classified: <br>
</p>
<p>2.1.1 No employee will receive a lower wage after the re-classification than he/she is receiving at present.<br>
</p>
<p>2.1.2 The re-classification of positions will be the subject of discussion between the NUM and the mine at mine level to 
ensure that fairness prevails.<br>
</p>
<p>2.1.3 The 1995 alignment exercise for non-staff employees at Douglas will also be applicable to staff employees to be 
re-classified as non-staff employees (i.e. the re-classification of employees should not create anomalies in non-staff 
categories).<br>
</p>
<p>2.1.4 Employees to be re-classified as non-staff employees will receive an increase equal to the agreed increase for their 
non-staff position.<br>
</p>
<p>2.2 <u>Process<br>
</u></p>
<p>The classification exercise will be executed as follows, prior to any increase being implemented for Douglas staff employees: <br>
</p>
<p>2.2.1 The Douglas management will submit a list containing the positions to be re-classified as non-staff occupations to the 
Ingwe/NUM Co-ordinators for consideration.<br>
</p>
<p>2.2.2 Once the list referred to above has been finalised, the employees concerned and who will be re-classified as non-staff 
employees, will be informed of their re-classification and of the increase they will receive.<br>
</p>
<p>2.2.3 The increase for the remaining staff employees will thereafter be implemented as per the agreement.<br>
</p>
<p>3. It is the intention of the parties to this agreement that the re-classification process be completed by 20 September 1996.<br>
<br>
</p>
<p align=center><a name="ANNEXUREB6"><font size=4><b>ANNEXURE B6<br>
</b></font></a><b></b></p>
<p><b><u>AGREEMENT BETWEEN GOLD MINES ADMINISTERED BY JCI LIMITED AND THE NATIONAL 
UNION OF MINEWORKERS<br>
</u></b>JCI Limited gold mines and the NUM believe that a variable increase linked to operational performance is appropriate at this 
time. Therefore the parties undertake to continue discussions at Divisional/Mine level on productivity linked variable 
remuneration aspects.<br>
</p>
