<HEAD>
<TITLE>Chamber of Minesof South Africa: Paid Education and Training Leave</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000080">
<a name="top"></a>
<center>
<IMG SRC="/images/logo2.gif"><p>

<FONT SIZE=5 COLOR=800040><B>PAID EDUCATION AND TRAINING LEAVE</B></FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3><B>AGREEMENT</B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=3 COLOR=008040>between</FONT><br>
<FONT SIZE=4 COLOR=008040><B>NATIONAL UNION OF MINEWORKERS</B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=3 COLOR=008040>and</FONT><br>
<FONT SIZE=4 COLOR=008040><B>CHAMBER OF MINES OF SOUTH AFRICA</B><P></FONT>



<IMG SRC="/images/linegr.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE><p>
<IMG SRC="/images/wd1.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE><br>


<FONT SIZE=4><B>I N D E X</B></FONT>
</center>

<blockquote>
<FONT SIZE=4><li><A HREF="#partie">Parties and Scope</a><br>
<li><A HREF="#recog">Recognition of Importance of Education and Training</A><br>
<li><A HREF="#guide">Guidelines</A><br>
<li><A HREF="#appro">Appropriate Level</A><br>
</blockquote>
<p>

<Center><IMG SRC="/images/linegr.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE><p></Center>

</b>
<p>

<A NAME="partie"></A>

<dl>
<dt><B>1. PARTIES AND SCOPE </B><BR>
1.1. It is recorded that this framework agreement is entered into by the Chamber on behalf of gold and coal mines, members of the Chamber, which recognise the NUM and by the NUM on behalf of its members employed in recognised bargaining units on such gold  and coal mines.<p>

<A NAME="recog"></A>
<dt><B>2. RECOGNITION OF IMPORTANCE OF EDUCATION AND TRAINING</B>
<dl>
<dt>2.1. The parties recognise that :<p>
<dl>
<dt>2.1.1.Employees seek to overcome illiteracy and improve learning skills in order to address past educational disadvantages.<p>

<dt>2.1.2.In order to achieve the goal of workplace efficiency and safety in the light of increasing pressures on viability and international competition, organisations need competent workforces with focused skills, and the flexibility to adapt to new work practices and technology.<p>
</dl>
<dt>2.2. Against this background the parties recognise that education and training in the industry is important in order to achieve relevant competencies and higher standards of performance subject to the operational requirements of each mine, and also to employees to facilitate access to opportunities in the workplace.<p>

<dt>2.3. The parties acknowledge that<p>

<dd>2.3.1. the right to education is a fundamental human right; and <p>

<dd>2.3.2. the primary responsibility for the provision of education lies with the State<p>

<dt>2.4. The parties accept that while the provision of training and education by employers must be directed by mine circumstances the discussions detailed in clause 4 will be informed by international standards and practice, including ILO Convention 140.<p>

<dt>2.5. The parties agree to review the practical implications for the mining industry of ILO Convention 140 following discussions detailed in clause 4 and in the NEDLAC Labour Market Chamber. <p>

<dt>2.6. In the event that the State formally ratifies ILO Convention 140 the parties agree to meet as part of the process of review set out in 2.5. above.  At the meeting the parties will discuss implementation by the State of the guidelines set out in the Convention and the implications for the mining industry.  This will take place in the light of the mine discussions taking place or having taken place at the appropriate level in terms of paragraph 3.1. as well as the process through Nedlac. <p></dl>


<A NAME="guide"></A>
<B>3. GUIDELINES</B><br>

<dt>3.1. In consideration of the above the parties agree that joint discussions should take place at the appropriate level identified in clause 4 below, on paid education and training in accordance with the following framework of guidelines : <p>
<dl>
<dt>3.1.1. Education and training within the industry aims to ensure that the employee has the necessary competence to perform his or her job effectively. <p>
<dt>3.1.2. Education and  training should be based on the operational requirements and constraints of the mine or company and the relevant developmental reuqirements of the employee in his/her career.<p>

<dt>3.1.3. Education and training need to take account of the levels of competence necessary for the job and the advancement of employees to higher competencies. <p>

<dt>3.1.4. Education and training need to be sufficiently flexible to accommodate changes in competencies required in the organisation of work.<p>

<dt>3.1.5. There is a need to identify jointly education and training programmes and courses that qualify in terms of these guidelines to be conducted during working hours on basic pay, or outside of working hours on a voluntary basis.<p>

<dt>3.1.6. All information relevant to discussions between the parties on education and training will be disclosed.<p>

<dt>3.1.7. There should be a regular and joint review of the education and training programmes referred to in 3.1.5.<p>

<dt>3.1.8. The discussions at the appropriate level shall commence and proceed as expeditiously as reasonably possible.<p>
</dl></dl>



<A NAME="appro"></A>
<B>4.  APPROPRIATE LEVEL</B><br><p>
The parties agree that the joint discussions referred to in 3.1. will take place between representatives of the NUM, of the one part, and each of the mining companies concerned, of the other part, at the appropriate level which is set out below:<p>

<B> Anglo American, Anglovaal, Gengold, Ingwe, JCI and Randgold</B> respectively<p>
Each mining company in the mining group concerned in a co-ordinated group forum and thereafter discussions on details with each mine.<p>

<B> Amcoal </b> <p>
Company is central forum<p>

<B> Alpha Anthracite, Duiker, Duiker Coal, Kangra and Gold Fields</b><p>

Mines in each group in a central forum subject to disucssions on details, where appropriate, at mine level.<p>  


<p>
<FONT SIZE=4 COLOR=800040><Center><B>Signed by the National Union of Mineworkers and the Chamber of Mines <br>on behalf of recognising mines at Johannesburg on this 8 day of February 1996.</B></Center></FONT>
<p>
<Center><IMG SRC="/images/linegr.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE><p></Center><br><p>

