<center><h3>Mining in South Africa's Nine Provinces</h3>
<b><i>Ranked by Mining Contribution to GGP:1993 and 1994</i></b></center>
<center><table border width=80%>
<tr> <th> Province<th> Mining Employees<th> GGP Mining Contribution<th> Total GGP R'000 000</tr>
<tr><th align=left> Northern Cape<th> 16 924<th> 44.6%<th> 7 303
<tr><th align=left> North West<th> 133 980<th> 42.3%<th> 18 960
<tr><th align=left> Mpumalanga<th> 86 759<th> 33.7%<th> 27 954
<tr><th align=left> Free State<th> 139 339<th> 28.6%<th> 21 397
<tr><th align=left> Northern Province<th> 37 971<th> 26.3%<th> 12 995
<tr><th align=left> Gauteng<th> 172 335<th> 6.2%<th> 130 386
<tr><th align=left> KwaZulu-Natal<th> 20 183<th> 2.4%<th> 51 429
<tr><th align=left> Western Cape<th> 11 488<th> 0.5%<th> 48 262
<tr><th align=left> Eastern Cape<th> 1 177<th> 0.2%<th> 26 226
</center></table>
