<center><h3>South Africa's Role in World Mineral Reserves</h3>
<b><i>As at 31 August 1994</i></b></center>
<center><table border width=50%>
<tr> <th> Commodity<th> % of World Reserves</tr>
<tr> <th align=left> Platinum Group Metals<th> 55%
<tr> <th align=left> Manganese<th> 83%
<tr> <th align=left> Chrome Ore<th> 73%
<tr> <th align=left> Vanadium<th> 45%
<tr> <th align=left> Vermiculite<th> 40%
<tr> <th align=left> Gold<th> 39%
<tr> <th align=left> Alumino-silicates<th> 37%
<tr> <th align=left> Zirconium Minerals<th> 26%
<tr> <th align=left> Fluorspar<th> 12%
<tr> <th align=left> Titanium Minerals<th> 11%
<tr> <th align=left> Coal<th> 11%
<tr> <th align=left> Nickel<th> 10%
<tr> <th align=left> Uranium<th> 8%
<tr> <th align=left> Phosphate Rock<th> 7%
<tr> <th align=left> Antimony<th> 5%
<tr> <th align=left> Zinc<th> 5%
</center></table>
