PALABORA's EARNINGS INCREASE 72% <I>(Sake-Beeld, Jhb)</I><BR>
The Palabora Copper Company took advantage of the higher copper price, increased production and lower real costs of production last year to earn 1 307c per share for its members, an increase of 72,4% from the previous financial year.<BR><P>
FINED OVER MUDSLIDE<I> (The Citizen, Jhb)</I><BR>
The Welkom regional court yesterday fined a third person, former Fraser Alexander regional manager Frikkie Botha, for negligence associated with the Merriespruit mudslide in 1994.<BR><P>
EAST DRIEFONTEIN FIRE:  104 MINERS EVACUATED<I> (The Citizen)</I><BR>
A fire broke out 2 200 m below the surface at the East Driefontein gold mine yesterday, causing 104 miners to be evacuated to refuge bays, the mine has reported.<BR><P>
DE BEERS, RUSSIA DEAL 'CLEVER'<I> (The Citizen, Jhb)</I><BR>
De Beers stands to strengthen its hold on the world market after reaching a co-operation agreement with Russia ensuring the company's position as the key buyer of Russian rough diamond exports, London analysts say.<BR><P>
ANGLO BREAKS UP JOHNNIC<I> (Sowetan,Jhb)</I><BR>
Anglo American is reported to be in the process of breaking down the unbundled pieces of JCI into smaller packages before selling them to black groups, and this has strengthened a longstanding suspicion among black businessmen that Anglo is not serious about unbundling.
