There is growing concern, even in ANC quarters, that the Labour Relations Act passed through Parliament last year will not create a climate conducive to achieving governments objectives of job creation and economic growth.<BR><P>
SA, MEXICO NOT IN THE SAME FIX<I> (Business Day)</I><BR>
SAs policymakers and economists have been at pains to point out why SA and Mexico are different animals.  Figures due for release this week should underline the fact that SAs fundamentals are in much better shape than Mexicos were at the time of the peso crash.<BR><P>
