PRIVATISATION BOGEYMAN OVER-INFLATED <I>(Business Times)</I><BR>
Worldwide plans to privatise state enterprises have inevitably led to clashes between trade unions and government.  South Africa is no exception.  Trade union action after the government first announced the partial or full privatisation of parastatals in December catapulted labour into action and eventually led to the signing of the National Framework Agreement this month.<BR><P>
CHINA GOLD, SILVER COIN SALES HIT RECORD IN 1995 <I>(Reuters)</I><BR>
BEIJING - Sales of gold and silver coins in China hit record highs in 1995, the China Business Weekly said on Sunday.<BR><P>
AUSTRALIAS GOLDCORP SETS MICKEY MOUSE IN GOLD <I>(Reuters)</I><BR>
PERTH - Australias largest gold refiner, Goldcorp, has launched a limited number of gold coins featuring Mickey and Minnie Mouse to mark 1996 as Year of the Rat in the Chinese lunar calendar. <BR><P>
