The chairman of Anglo American Industrial Corporation, Leslie Boyd, on Tuesday said countries such as Indonesia and Hungary, where wages were one-fifth of those in SA, were attractive prospects for foreign investment.<BR><P>
SLOW LIFTING OF CONTROLS LIKELY <I>(Business Report)</I><BR>
