<TITLE>Chamber of Mines of South Africa: Mining News</TITLE></head>
 <BODY  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000080"><Center><b><center><b><h1><b><font size=4>MONDAY, 11 MARCH 1996 - at 11H00 GMT+2</b></h1></b></center></center><BR><P>


CANADAS BARRICK TO STICK WITH GOLD HEDGING STRATEGY <I> (Business Times,Sun.)</I><BR>
Barrick Gold, third largest of the worlds gold producers, last year earned an additional $69,4m in revenue from an astute hedging programme.  The Canadian company earned $22/ounce more than if it  had sold at spot market prices.  In the past eight years hedging has added an extra $409m to its revenue.<BR><P>
<A HREF="http://www.bullion.org.za/safebill.htm">TALKS ON MINE SAFETY</A><I> (Business Day, Jhb)</I><BR>
Mining companies would negotiate outstanding safety issues this week in a draft Mine Health and Safety bill, COM president At du Plessis said yesterday.<BR><P>
GOLD LIKELY TO STAY ABOVE $390<I> (Business Report, Jhb)</I><BR>
The demand for gold from consumers was likely to keep the metal from falling to below the $390m-an-ounce level although it fell to two-month lows last week, analysts and traders said at the weekend.<BR><P>
DUBAI GOLD EXPECTED TO ATTRACT INDIAN BUYING <I>(Reuters)</I><BR>
DUBAI - Indian and Middle East Gulf demand for imports of gold from the leading Gulf re-export centre of Dubai is expected to increase after last weeks dip in international gold prices, Dubai bullion traders said.<BR><P>
RISING GOLD SUPPLY GAP MAY NOT LIFT PRICES-REPORT <I>(Reuters)</I><BR>
LONDON - The gold market supply deficit rose to 700tonnes last year, but that did not mean prices had to rise, a brokers report this week said.  Several factors hinted that interpreting the deficit as a bullish factor could be dangerous, according to the report from Merrill Lynch Futures Research.<BR><P>
CHINA PROVINCES INCREASE GOLD OUTPUT TARGETS <I>(Reuters)</I><BR>
BEIJING - Chinas leading gold producers have vowed to increase gold production and develop new gold resources in the 1996-2000 Ninth Five-Year Plan, Xinhua news agency said on Sunday.<BR><P>
GOLD PRICE, TAKEOVERS TO DOMINATE GOLD MEETING <I>(Reuters)</I><BR>
PERTH - When 450 delegates gather in Australias gold mining capital of Kalgoorlie for the Australian Gold Conference this week, two topics will dominate:  Where will the price of gold go after the fading bull run early this year, and what comes next in the recent burst of corporate activity in the Australian gold sector?<BR><P>
FIRE IN MINE EXTINGUISHED<I> (Beeld, Jhb)</I><BR>
The Driefontein gold mine says the underground fire that broke out in a section of the mine on 28 February has been extinguished.<BR><P>
BLYVOORUITZICHT'S OFFER<I> (Beeld)</I><BR>
In its planned rights issue of R410-million, Blyvooruitzicht is going to give shareholders the choice of applying for 15 linked units at 600c per unit for each 100 shares already held.<BR><P>
GENGOLD STILL DISCUSSING <I> (Beeld)</I><BR>
Gengold says discussions are still being held on the amalgamation of its mines in the Evander area into a large new mine.<BR><P>
HARMONY GOLD MINE ROBBED<I> (The Citizen, Jhb)</I><BR>
The offices of the Harmony gold mine at Virginia were robbed by four armed men on Friday, and a large but as yet undetermined amount of money is missing.<BR><P>

