<TITLE>Chamber of Mines of South Africa: Mining News</TITLE></head>
 <BODY  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000080"><Center><b><center><b><b><font size=4>MONDAY, 5 AUGUST 1996 - at 11H00 GMT+2 </font></b></b></center></center>
<BR><P>




MBOWENI URGES MINERS TO ACCEPT REINSTATEMENT <I>(Business Day, Jhb)</I><BR>
Labour Minister Tito Mboweni has urged workers dismissed from Rustenburg Platinum Mines after going on an illegal strike a month ago to accept reinstatement in a bid to resolve the acrimonious labour dispute at the mine, which left a security guard dead last week.<BR><P>
SA, ZIMBABWE DEAL BOLSTERS AFRICAN TRADE TALKS <I>(Business Day)</I><BR>
The export tariff agreement on textiles and clothing forged between SA and Zimbabwe last week would bolster SAs chances of concluding a single trade protocol with its southern African partners.<BR><P>
MINORCO SECURES FUNDING FOR $1,7BN PROJECT IN CHILE <I>(Business Day)</I><BR>
Anglo American's offshore arm Minorco is to restart operations at Chilean gold concern Marte, and has also secured funding for a $1,7bn Chilean copper project Collahuasi.<BR><P>
HOPES RISE OVER OFFSHORE NAMIBIAN GAS FIELD<I>(Business Day)</I><BR>
One of the most eagerly awaited gas exploration wells in Africa will finally break ground 150km off the southern Namibian coast this week.<BR><P>
DE BEERS SEEKS THE SALES OF NEW CANADIAN MINES <I>(Business Day)</I><BR>
De Beers is courting new diamond producers in Canada in a bid to persuade them to market their output through its Central Selling Organisation (CSO).<BR><P>
STALS CALM OVER WEAKER FOREX RESERVES <I>(Business Day)</I><BR>
Yuppie currency traders in London have been scoffing at SA's foreign exchange reserves, saying the Reserve Bank has not the cash to defend the currency.  Nevertheless, Bank governor Chris Stals is not losing any sleep over the forex reserves - even though forecasts indicate a fall in July.<BR><P>
GOVT BEHIND RANDGOLD REFINERY PLAN <I>(Business Day)</I><BR>
The Trade and Industry Department has thrown its weight behind Randgold's plan to sell gold produced from a proposed refinery at its Harmony Gold Mine.<BR><P>
ELECTRICITY OUTPUT RISE SIGNALS GROWTH <I>(Business Report, Jhb)</I><BR>
The accelerated growth in electricity generation in the second quarter of the year is evidence that the economy is not slowing down as sharply as people think, Econometrix, the economics consultancy, said last week.<BR><P>
BUSINESS CONCERNED OVER CSS <I>(Business Report)</I><BR>
Concern that restructuring at the Central Statistical Service (CSS) may be undermining the quality and scope of its service to business has prompted Business South Africa (BSA) to request a meeting with the senior management of the CSS.<BR><P>
S AFRICAN GOLD MINES IN Q2 <I>(Reuters)</I><BR>
JOHANNESBURG - The overriding conclusion is that the gold industry was floated to a higher level of profitability entirely through the depreciation of the rand in the second quarter.  Of course, this has generally been the case in the last 15 years or so of the industry's decline.<BR><P>
JOB STRIFE PLAGUES SOUTH AFRICAN MINING INDUSTRY <I>(Reuters)</I><BR>
JOHANNESBURG - South Africa's vast mining industry was in the grip of mounting job strife on Friday, with production hit at leading platinum mines and the prospect of industrial action spreading to gold and coal.<BR><P>
