ASIAN CURRENCIES 'WILL STAY CLOSE TO DOLLAR' <I>(Business Day)</I><BR>
SINGAPORE - Asian currencies are unlikely to give up their ties with the dollar in a hurry as the region's countries continue to face shifting economic and political landscapes next year, economists say.<BR><P>
