GOLD HELPS SYFRETS TO TOP UNIT TRUST PERFORMERS <I>(Business Day)</I><BR>
Syfrets mining and resources fund was the top performing unit trust this year with a 44,74% return following a spectacular first half-year for gold shares, the latest Micropal figures show.<BR><P>
ZAIRE REBELS GIVE ULTIMATUM TO GOLD MINERS <I>(Reuters)</I><BR>
GOMA, ZAIRE - Rebels controlling a large area of eastern Zaire have ordered gold miners in the area to come forward and discuss the future of their mining concessions by January 3 or risk losing their assets.<BR><P>
CHINESE GOLD DEMAND AT 330 TONNES IN '97 <I>(Reuters)</I><BR>
LONDON - Chinese gold consumption could be about 330 tonnes in 1997 compared with a forecast 280 tonnes this year, says Andy Smith in Union Bank of Switzerland's latest Precious Metals Outlook.<BR><P>
CONSTRUCTION OF STEEL MILL SUFFERS ANOTHER SETBACK <I>(Business Day)</I><BR>
Construction of the R6,8bn steel mill at Saldanha Bay could be set back following the dismissal of 30% of its construction workforce who embarked on an illegal strike over transport home for Christmas.<BR><P>
