Diamond exploration and development company Trans Hex International, a subsidiary of the Trans Hex Group, will begin trading on the Toronto Stock Exchange on Friday and not Thursday as previously announced, the group said.<BR><P>
GOLD SEEN TRADING IN $340-425 RANGE <I>(Reuters)</I><BR>
DUESSELDORF - Gold bullion prices in 1997 were seen in a very broad trading range of $340 to $425 dollars per ounce amid high volatility, WestLB Bank said in a report.<BR><P>
CENTRAL BANKS CAST BIG SHADOW OVER 1997 GOLD PRICE <I>(Reuters)</I><BR>
