PREDICTIONS FOR 1997 <I>(Business Mail, Fridays with the Mail & Guardian)</I><BR>
It's not all doom and gloom on the economic front, but the govt must start putting its policies into practice to boost confidence.  Hindsight, as the economic fraternity learnt this year, is an exact science.  To a man - and woman - they got it badly wrong in 1996, but then nobody anticipated the currency crisis.<BR><P>
JUNIOR VS GIANTS <I>(Business Mail)</I><BR>
