<A NAME="topics"></A>
<H4>TOPICS</H4>
Major topics will include:
<ul>
<li>      Mine System Simulation
<li>       Artificial Intelligence
<li>       Expert Systems
<li>       Virtual Reality
<li>       Neural Networks
<li>       Robotics 
</ul>
Attempts will be made to obtain papers dealing with the historical development of these
topics with current mining applications.<p><p>
<p>
<center>
<a href="/main.htm"> <IMG SRC="/nb1.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE border=0 alt="Main Menu" hspace=20></a>
<a href="#top"> <IMG SRC="/nb2.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE border=0 alt="Top of Page" hspace=20></a>
<a href="#toolbar"> <IMG SRC="/nb3.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE border=0 alt="Toolbar" hspace=20></a>
</center><br><br><p>
<A NAME="format"></A>
<H4>SYMPOSIUM FORMAT</H4>

All professionals who work or carry out research on the symposium's topics are invited to
participate. Abstracts for proposed papers should be submitted by 1 June 1996.  All
abstracts should be sent via e-mail to both symposium chairmen. Accepted papers will be
published on the Internet between 2-13 December 1996, which are the symposium dates.<p>

A Web site will be set up and maintained at NTUA, which will provide the technical support
for the symposium. Over the symposium period, participants will be able to use this Web
site to tune in, or tune out and in again, many times; to read and download papers, to
"write in" their comments, queries and criticisms. These will be entered and available for
all to see. Papers' authors will periodically defend their theses and offer comments to
queries or criticisms.  There is no cost for this symposium.  No "conference fees". No
"traveling costs".<p>

The symposium site at NTUA can be accessed through the Mining Systems Simulation
Lab's Home Page on:<p>

    <a href="http://www.metal.ntua.gr/msslab/MineSim96/index.html</a><p>

You may care to explore this home site now.  Please do not forget to register!  Once
registered you can enter this site at will. During the pre-symposium period this site will
keep you informed on symposium's status and provide useful information to tentative
participants.  The proceedings of the conference will be available on CD at nominal cost. <p><p>

<center>
<a href="/main.htm"> <IMG SRC="/nb1.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE border=0 alt="Main Menu" hspace=20></a>
<a href="#top"> <IMG SRC="/nb2.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE border=0 alt="Top of Page" hspace=20></a>
<a href="#toolbar"> <IMG SRC="/nb3.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE border=0 alt="Toolbar" hspace=20></a>
</center><br><br><p><p><p>


